gov.usgs.comcat

Class ComCatEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.comcat.ComCatEvent

  • public class ComCatEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    This class returns QuakeML from the earthquake.usgs.gov website given an event ID. The quake ML is parsed into local variables fro things like preferred magnitudes, depth, epicenter, etc and builds a list of picks from the events with the basic information. Normal Usage :
    1) create the ComCatEvent object and optionally set the base URL to something like "https://earthquake.usgs.gov/fdsnws/"
    2) Optionally use setEvent() to set the eventID, start and end times, or change the format (do not change the format only XML is supported!)
    3) Optionally use setLatLongLimit() to pick a geographic region
    4) Call executeURL() to fetch the data from the FDSN server, this will return the length of the returned document
    5) call parseQuakeML() to marshal/parse the QuakeML document returned, this will return the number of events in the document
    6) For simple parsing, call getEvent(int n) for each event starting with zero and process the events using the getter functions
    7) call clearURL() to start over and setup to start a new request
    There are advanced usage methods to get the full QuakeML object or the preferred origin as a JAXB object, or to get the full text of the QuakeML document.
    Picks can be obtained by NSCL by calling "getPick(NSCl)" or an ArrayList of Simple picks is available from getPicksList(); The other getter methods return preferred magnitudes, origin information parse out from the document. Since there are many origins and magnitudes only the preferred ones are picked apart. To process all of the origins or magnitudes get the origin or magnitudes list as JAXB objects from the

      • getEvent

        public Event getEvent(int nevent)
        Get the nth event from the document and this event is returned as a JAXB event object. You can use the returne object to get to all of the JAXB representation of the object. JAXB uses a lot of lists based on the QuakeML xsd definitions. You can see in this code how the preferred information is picked out from the list of origins, mags, etc and how to process the picks.
        Parameters:
        nevent - THe event number from zero to the number of events
        Returns:
        The event object just positioned.
